My project uses an Arduino UNO with 11 LEDs connected to digital pins 2 through 12. The animation runs in two phases:
Phase 1 – Outside In (Left & Right → Middle)
Two LEDs light up at the same time — one from the left end and one from the right end. They turn off, then the next inner pair lights up, and so on, until both sides meet at the middle LED. This creates a "converging" or closing-in effect.
Phase 2 – Inside Out (Middle → Left & Right)
The animation reverses. Starting from the middle LED, pairs light up moving outward toward both ends simultaneously, creating an "expanding" or opening effect.
The two phases repeat in a continuous loop, giving the appearance of LEDs bouncing back and forth from the edges to the center and back again.
